<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-781-392  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 781 392.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>IBM System User  May 1990 p21(4).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Doing more with less. (automation of UK's Standard Chartered Bank)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Goodwin, Candice.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The UK's Standard Chartered Bank is automating its data centeroperations in hopes of providing high quality, cost effectiveservice from its five international information centers.andP;  PhilReed, manager of the bank's technology directorate, believes thebank will save between 18 and 20 million pounds by 1995.andP;  StandardChartered created its own automation package by combining the bestcommercial packages with the bank's own software.andP;  The automationproject will be completed in four stages.andP;  Phase one, whichaddresses high-end services, has been in place since summer 1989.andO;Phase two, involving automated scheduling, and phase three, whichwill introduce security facilities, message processing and statuschecking, should be in operation by late 1990.andP;  Phase four,including contingency recovery, inventory management and automaticfault diagnosis, is slated for spring 1991.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Standard Chartered Bank PLC (management).andO;Topic:     BankingAutomationUnited KingdomInformation CentersManagement of EDPProject ManagementMISSystem Selection.andO;Feature:   illustrationportrait.andO;Caption:   Phil Reed (portrait)Person:    Reed, Phil (management).andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>